Howdy yall,

We are working on setting up PathPlanner in simulation. We are loading the paths from file, then converting them to trajectories. We are putting the x and y desired chassis speeds from the trajectory on smart dashboard to be plotted in advantage scope. The desired speeds appear to be very jittery, jumping between a velocity which makes sense, and one much slower. Any idea why this is happening?

Now im just talking to myself. We replaced
path.generateTrajectory(new ChassisSpeeds(), path.getInitialHeading(), RobotConfig.fromGUISettings());
with
path.getIdealTrajectory(RobotConfig.fromGUISettings())
and that fixed the pre made path issues, but generating paths on the fly still is very jittery
